prefix_rule(pattern=["/usr/bin/zsh", "-lc", "gh issue create --label needs-triage --label infra --title \"Vitest teardown race in outbounds.test.ts\" --body $'> *Drafted by AI. Review before merging.*\\n\\n**Category:** infra\\n\\n## Trigger surface\\n\\nRun `npm test` locally or in CI with the Convex/Vitest suite.\\n\\n## Observable outcome\\n\\nThe test run reports all tests passing but intermittently prints `EnvironmentTeardownError: [vitest-worker]: Closing rpc while \"onUserConsoleLog\" was pending`, attributed to `convex/outbounds.test.ts`.\\n\\n## Problem\\n\\n`FINDINGS.md` captured an intermittent Vitest-level teardown race from #139. The error appears after the suite passes and is not tied to a failing assertion, but it pollutes test output and can hide real teardown failures.\\n\\n## Acceptance criteria\\n\\n- Reproduce or characterize the teardown race enough to distinguish Vitest/convex-test teardown timing from an application test failure.\\n- Add a targeted mitigation, such as a `globalTeardown` delay or a dependency/version update, only if it removes the intermittent error without masking real failures.\\n- Document the exact test command and before/after evidence in the issue/PR notes.\\n- Do not suppress test failures or swallow console errors globally.'"], decision="allow")
prefix_rule(pattern=["gh", "run", "view"], decision="allow")
prefix_rule(pattern=["/usr/bin/zsh", "-lc", "gh issue create --label needs-triage --label bug --title \"Guard notification deep-link navigation against double-fire\" --body $'> *Drafted by AI. Review before merging.*\\n\\n**Category:** bug\\n\\n## Trigger surface\\n\\nLO clicks a notification action that deep-links from `/notifications` to a file flag surface, such as `Review flag` for `fitness-pursuit-exhausted` or `Review LOE` for `borrower-signed-loe-filed`.\\n\\n## Observable outcome\\n\\nThe app navigates once to `/file/$fileId/flags` and resets the selected notification id so the action can be clicked again later.\\n\\n## Problem\\n\\n`FlagDeepLinkMount` and `ArtifactDeepLinkMount` in `src/routes/notifications.tsx` both navigate from a query-backed `useEffect`. The current `onNavigated` reset should prevent repeated navigation, but it depends on the reset landing before a second render/effect pass. React StrictMode or memoization churn can double-fire the navigation while the resolved query result is still set.\\n\\n## Acceptance criteria\\n\\n- Add an idempotence guard, likely a `useRef(false)`, inside both deep-link mounts.\\n- Reset the guard appropriately when `flagId`/`artifactId` changes so re-clicking the same action later still works.\\n- Cover both flag and artifact notification paths with a focused test or documented manual verification.\\n- Keep the existing route target `/file/$fileId/flags` and selected-id reset behavior.'"], decision="allow")
prefix_rule(pattern=["/usr/bin/zsh", "-lc", "gh issue create --label needs-triage --label feature --title \"Resolve dormant ProposeArtifact engine intention\" --body $'> *Drafted by AI. Review before merging.*\\n\\n**Category:** enhancement\\n\\n## Trigger surface\\n\\nRun a file-engine sweep for a file whose facts and flags would require a new LOE or other Artifact Decision.\\n\\n## Observable outcome\\n\\nThe shipped architecture either has a real production path that emits `ProposeArtifact`, or the engine intention union/applier no longer expose a dormant `ProposeArtifact` path.\\n\\n## Problem\\n\\n`FINDINGS.md` captured that `convex/engine/types.ts` still exports `ProposeArtifactIntention` and `convex/engine/applyDelta/index.ts` still routes it through `applyProposeArtifact`, but no current engine generator emits `ProposeArtifact`. The path is load-bearing only for standalone `artifacts.createFromIntention` callers, so the file-engine sweep architecture and runtime code have drifted.\\n\\n## Acceptance criteria\\n\\n- Decide one direction and implement it: remove `ProposeArtifact` from the engine union/applier and make `createFromIntention` a standalone entry point, or reintroduce a generator that emits `ProposeArtifact` from a real artifact-readiness condition.\\n- Update `ARCHITECTURE.md` and `docs/architecture/engine/decisions.md` to remove the temporary drift note once the code is settled.\\n- Add or update tests proving the chosen runtime behavior.\\n- Verify no production path still depends on a dormant engine intention.'"], decision="allow")
